<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="828" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14487.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Brazilian Minister, Mexico City, telegraphs International Relief
                            Committee has 250,000 pesos for purchase supplies at Pachuca, San Juan
                            del Rio and Apam, but unable obtain railway transportation. Immediately
                            request Carranza facilitate transportation much needed supplies.
                            Telegraph Minister result your efforts.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>